      FUD
   =20
 =20
One way to do fraud when you are pitching an investment is to lie about the=
 investment. =E2=80=9COur thing has guaranteed 20% monthly returns with no =
risk,=E2=80=9D you say, and then you steal all the money. This is pretty co=
mmon.Another=C2=A0way to do fraud when you are pitching an investment is to=
 lie about the=C2=A0alternatives. =E2=80=9CIf you put money in a bank or th=
e stock market it will all be stolen from you by vampires; only our thing c=
an protect you from that.=E2=80=9D (Then you steal all the money.) This is =
=E2=80=A6 also pretty common? A lot of financial frauds seem to appeal to p=
eople with a conspiratorial mind-set; they are happy to believe that the re=
gular system is stacked against them and they need to give their money to a=
 scammer to protect themselves.=C2=A0It probably will not surprise you much=
 to learn that an alleged gold-coin-investing scam allegedly did both. Here=
=E2=80=99s a U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission enforcement action aga=
inst Safeguard Metals LLC and its owner Jeffrey Santulan; from the complain=
t:Guided by scripts, some of which were prepared by Santulan, Safeguard sal=
es agents made false and misleading statements to investors about the purpo=
rted risks associated with the investors=E2=80=99 existing securities holdi=
ngs at investment banks and brokerage firms. For example, Safeguard=E2=80=
=99s sales agents stated that a =E2=80=9CMoney Market Reform Law=E2=80=9D a=
llowed banks and brokerage firms to freeze retirement accounts in the event=
 of a market downturn; that top financial experts in the United States were=
 saying that another recession was coming very soon; and that when that hap=
pened, the investors=E2=80=99 accounts would be frozen and they would not b=
e able to get any money out of their 401(k) plans or Individual Retirement =
Accounts (=E2=80=9CIRAs=E2=80=9D). These statements were misleading because=
, among other things, the law that Safeguard referenced applied only to mon=
ey market funds in rare circumstances and could not result in an individual=
=E2=80=99s entire account being frozen.Honestly if you were susceptible to =
Safeguard=E2=80=99s pitch this is not very reassuring?Scammer: A new law al=
lows the government to freeze your retirement accounts! Buy gold!You: Ooh t=
hat sounds bad.The SEC: Actually that law only applies in rare circumstance=
s.You:=C2=A0Somehow that sounds worse?Really if all they did was misreprese=
nt the importance of money-market-fund reform I feel like they=E2=80=99d ha=
ve a decent defense? That would be a fun trial to do, like, the SEC puts yo=
u on trial for lying about the safety of the traditional financial system, =
and you turn around and put the traditional financial system on trial. Also=
 though:Safeguard and Santulan also allegedly misled investors about Safegu=
ard=E2=80=99s commissions and markups on the coins, charging average markup=
s of approximately 64% on its sales of silver coins, instead of the 4% to 3=
3% markups that they disclosed to investors. According to the complaint, Sa=
feguard obtained approximately $67 million from the sale of coins to more t=
han 450 mostly elderly, retail investors, and kept approximately $25.5 mill=
ion in mark ups.And:Safeguard=E2=80=99s sales agents, in calls to potential=
 investors, lied about their investment experience and qualifications. For =
example, in a script provided to safeguard=E2=80=99s sales agents, an =E2=
=80=9Copener=E2=80=9D sales agent was directed to introduce a =E2=80=9Cclos=
er=E2=80=9D sales agent to the potential investor as a =E2=80=9Csenior repr=
esentative [who] has been helping retirees/conservatives protect their weal=
th for over 17 years now, including back in =E2=80=9908. He actually specia=
lizes in 401k/IRAs and has far more expertise on your particular situation.=
=E2=80=9D None of Safeguard=E2=80=99s employees had experience remotely fit=
ting that description.That=E2=80=99s harder to defend.
