f its holdings. Less than 10% stemmed from investor withdrawals, and the fu=
nd ended the month with $13 billion in assets. With a day=E2=80=99s worth o=
f flow data in January still to come, the ETF had posted net inflows in 202=
2, even as it slumped about 20%.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">=E2=80=9CShe lost so much cash but kept so many investors=E2=80=9D is pe=
